<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19950] Relation#toRestriction() may not handle ReversedType properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19950</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;o.a.c.cql3.Relation#toRestriction()&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;ClusterMetadata#type&lt;/tt&gt; directly but this type can be &lt;tt&gt;ReverseType&lt;/tt&gt;, which seems to bypass most of the checks. Checks like &lt;tt&gt;isMultiCell()&lt;/tt&gt; can be hard to spot as clustering keys don&apos;t allow multi-cell, but then we do checks like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;checkFalse(column.type instanceof ListType, &quot;Indexes on list entries (%s[index] = value) are not supported.&quot;, column.name);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the column is reversed clustering then this check always returns &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt;, even if it&apos;s a reverse list!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
