                            <comment id="17884337" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2024 15:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt; Discovered this while testing Accord in &lt;tt&gt;cep-15-accord&lt;/tt&gt; after the recent rebase, but it should be a problem on &lt;tt&gt;trunk&lt;/tt&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17884339" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2024 15:50:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blerer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blerer&quot;&gt;blerer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17884344" author="dcapwell" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2024 15:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I imple the is* methods for reverse type just to add a break point, then ran my queries and hit this.  The query was an UPDATE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17884347" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2024 16:01:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A poem by Microsoft Copilot, courtesy of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;In Cassandra&#8217;s realm, where data flows, A reverse type brings woe and woes. For clustering keys, it twists the tale, Making reads and writes often fail. Efficiency drops, performance lags, Queries slow, and patience sags. Ascending order is the way, For swift retrieval, night and day. So heed this warning, wise and clear, Avoid reverse, keep data near. In Cassandra&#8217;s world, let order reign, For speed and grace, and lessened pain.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17884348" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2024 16:06:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This may predate &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19341&quot; title=&quot;Relation and Restriction hierarchies are too complex and error prone&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. If it does, we might consider expanding the versions for this one or just creating a separate Jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885192" author="maedhroz" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2024 02:05:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible repro from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Override &lt;tt&gt;isMultiCell()&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;ReverseType&lt;/tt&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;@Test
public void repo()
{
    createTable(&quot;CREATE TABLE %s (pk int, ck frozen&amp;lt;list&amp;lt;int&amp;gt;&amp;gt;, v int, PRIMARY KEY(pk, ck)) WITH CLUSTERING ORDER BY (ck DESC)&quot;);
    execute(&quot;UPDATE %s SET v=42 WHERE pk=? AND ck=?&quot;, 0, Arrays.asList(0));
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
